
[1]simulation

   SIMULA'TION, n. [L. simulation.] The act of feigning to be that which
   is not; the assumption of a deceitful appearance or character.
   Simulation differs from dissimulation. The former denotes the assuming
   of a false character; the latter denotes the concealment of the true
   character. Both are comprehended in the word hypocrisy.
